11. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have some or all of the following rights regarding your personal data. To exercise any of these rights, contact us at privacy@stratum.dev.
11.1 Rights Under GDPR (EEA, UK, and Switzerland Residents)
•	Right of access: You can request a copy of all personal data we hold about you.
•	Right of rectification: You can ask us to correct inaccurate personal data.
•	Right of erasure: You can ask us to delete your personal data. For Free tier users: deletion of your account deletes all associated data. For Team/Enterprise: subject to any data retention obligations and your employer's instructions.
•	Right to data portability: You can request your account data in a machine-readable format.
•	Right to object: You can object to processing based on legitimate interests.
•	Right to withdraw consent: For NL processing and telemetry (consent-based), you can withdraw at any time as described in Sections 5.5 and 7.3.
•	Right to lodge a complaint: You have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.

11.2 Rights Under CCPA (California Residents)
California residents have the right to know what personal information we collect, the right to delete personal information, the right to opt out of the sale of personal information (Stratum does not sell personal information), and the right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights.
To submit a CCPA request: privacy@stratum.dev or toll-free at [PHONE NUMBER].

12. Children's Privacy
Stratum is not directed at children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 16. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact privacy@stratum.dev and we will delete it promptly.

13. Security
Stratum takes the security of your data seriously:
•	Source files and project models never leave your machine, so they are not exposed to our infrastructure at all.
•	Account data (Team/Enterprise) is stored encrypted at rest (AES-256) and transmitted over TLS 1.3.
•	Stratum does not store passwords — authentication uses third-party identity providers (GitHub OAuth, Google OAuth, or SSO for Enterprise).
•	We conduct annual security assessments of our infrastructure.
•	We operate a responsible disclosure program at security@stratum.dev. Verified security researchers who report vulnerabilities in good faith will not face legal action.
To report a security vulnerability: security@stratum.dev. We aim to acknowledge reports within 48 hours and resolve critical vulnerabilities within 7 days.

